<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbddcacc7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6953"><num value="6953">§ 6953.</num><heading> Development of markets for recovered materials</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Commerce shall within two years after <date date="1979-09-01">September 1, 1979</date>, take such actions as may be necessary to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbddcacc8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6953/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> identify the geographical location of existing or potential markets for recovered materials;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbddcacc9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6953/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> identify the economic and technical barriers to the use of recovered materials; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbddf1dca-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6953/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> encourage the development of new uses for recovered materials.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbddf1dcb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/272/tII/s5003">Pub. L. 89–272, title II, § 5003</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/94/580/s2">Pub. L. 94–580, § 2</ref>, <date date="1976-10-21">Oct. 21, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2821">90 Stat. 2821</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/96/482/s21/b">Pub. L. 96–482, § 21(b)</ref>, <date date="1980-10-21">Oct. 21, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2346">94 Stat. 2346</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbddf1dcc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
